
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-vgovindan-l2vpn-evpn-bfd-02.txt'>
    <title>"Proactive fault detection in EVPN", Vengada Govindan, Samer Salam, Ali Sajassi</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-vgovindan-l2vpn-evpn-bfd-02.txt</link>
    <description>This document proposes a proactive, in-band network OAM mechanism to detect connectivity faults that affect unicast and multi-destination paths in an EVPN network.  The multi-destination paths are used by Broadcast, unknown Unicast and Multicast (BUM) traffic.  The mechanisms proposed in the draft use the principles of the widely adopted Bidirectional Forwarding Detection (BFD) protocol.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-07-04T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
